  <prompt>
    Build the new `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` — a Workspace-pane widget that
    renders structured AI output progressively via `FieldDelta` SSE events. This
    widget is on the R5 critical path (per TASK-INDEX.md §Critical Path) and is
    BOTH the destination for Summarize streaming output (FR-02) AND the
    destination for Insights playbook + RAG static-response rendering (FR-13 /
    D2-16). The same widget renders both via different schemas — that
    "schema-driven" design is the load-bearing reuse claim of R5's platform
    extensibility story and is explicitly flagged as risk UR-02.

    The widget is React 19, lives in `@spaarke/ai-widgets`, follows the Fluent
    UI v9 semantic-token + dark-mode discipline of ADR-021, registers via the
    existing `WorkspaceWidgetRegistry` pattern (see `register-document-viewer-widget.ts`),
    and subscribes to the three additive PaneEventBus event types added by task
    016 (`workspace.streaming_started`, `workspace.field_delta`,
    `workspace.streaming_complete`) per ADR-030 additive discipline.

    Per R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 reuse mandate: use existing Fluent UI v9 primitives
    (`Card`, `Text`, `Badge`, `MessageBar`, `Skeleton`) — do NOT build a parallel
    UI primitive library. Per UR-02 mitigation: handle the Summarize + Insights
    playbook schemas first; document edge cases for follow-up rather than
    over-generalize. Apply 80/20 to display hints.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior React 19 + Fluent UI v9 widget developer with experience building
    streaming AI output components (token-progressive rendering, SSE
    subscription, JSON-path-keyed deltas). Familiar with Spaarke's
    `@spaarke/ai-widgets` package, `WorkspaceWidgetRegistry` pattern, and the
    PaneEventBus additive event-type discipline (ADR-030).
  </role>

  <goal>
    `StructuredOutputStreamWidget.tsx` and `register-structured-output-stream-widget.ts`
    are committed to `src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/`.
    The widget: (1) accepts a render schema (top-level field list + per-field
    display hints) via `widgetData`; (2) subscribes to PaneEventBus
    `workspace.field_delta` events keyed by JSON path and appends content as
    deltas arrive (ChatGPT/Claude-style cursor animation — NOT plop); (3)
    transitions cleanly between four distinct render states (streaming /
    streaming-complete / decline / empty-result); (4) is registered under
    `'structured-output-stream'` widget type via `registerWorkspaceWidget()`;
    (5) passes dark-mode visual check (Fluent v9 semantic tokens only); (6)
    passes the FULL-rigor quality gates (`code-review` + `adr-check`).

    Reusability acceptance: a follow-up Insights task (D2-16 / task 026) MUST
    be able to render an Insights playbook envelope by passing only a different
    schema config — no widget code change required for the second consumer.
  </goal>

