  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent UI v9 semantic tokens ONLY — no hex/rgba/Fluent v8 imports. Dark mode MUST be tested and pass; the four render states MUST all be legible against both `webLightTheme` and `webDarkTheme`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React 19 only — functional component + hooks; no class components; no legacy React idioms (`React.FC` typing acceptable but `React.JSX.Element` return preferred over `JSX.Element`).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Lives in `@spaarke/ai-widgets` shared library. Context-agnostic — no `Xrm` references, no PCF-specific imports, no SpaarkeAi-shell-specific imports.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-030">PaneEventBus is closed at 4 channels. R5 adds event types WITHIN the existing `workspace` channel (`streaming_started`, `field_delta`, `streaming_complete`). MUST NOT add a 5th channel. Existing subscribers ignore unknown discriminants — preserve this by emitting only the documented event-type discriminants.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">No token snapshots. This widget does NOT call BFF directly — it consumes streamed events delivered via PaneEventBus from upstream dispatchers (the chat-pane SSE consumer in SpaarkeAi). If a future evolution requires BFF calls, use `authenticatedFetch` from `@spaarke/auth`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism — N/A for frontend widget. Confirm in task notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">BFF publish-size — N/A; this task adds frontend code only. Confirm publish-size delta = 0 MB in task notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 reuse mandate">MUST use existing Fluent UI v9 primitives (`Card`, `CardHeader`, `Text`, `Badge`, `MessageBar`, `Skeleton`, `Divider`). MUST NOT build a parallel UI primitive library. Cite the primitive used in code comments.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.4">Subscribes to event types added by task 016 (`workspace.streaming_started`, `workspace.field_delta`, `workspace.streaming_complete`). Import the additive types from `PaneEventTypes.ts` — do NOT redefine.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec UR-02">Schema-driven complexity is flagged risk. Apply 80/20: handle Summarize schema + Insights playbook schema concretely first; document edge cases for follow-up. Do NOT over-generalize to a fully arbitrary JSON renderer.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-02">Acceptance: `AnalysisChunk.Type = "delta"` events arrive as `FieldDelta { path, content, sequence }`; widget renders each field progressively (cursor animation, NOT plop); existing wizard consumers unaffected.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Widget MUST handle out-of-order `FieldDelta` events safely (use `sequence` to detect, log if drop required). Append-only semantics for `content` per `path`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Decline-state and empty-result-state rendering MUST be visually distinct from streaming-complete success. Decline uses `MessageBar` with `intent="warning"`; empty-result uses muted `Text` with hint copy. No raw stack traces.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">No `any` types in public exports. Schema, widget data, and event payloads are fully typed.</constraint>
  </constraints>

