    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Workspace widget registration (canonical)" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/register-document-viewer-widget.ts">
        Exports a string constant for the widget type key, calls
        `registerWorkspaceWidget(KEY, { displayName, category, icon, allowMultiple, defaultOrder }, () => import('./Widget'))`,
        and exports a sentinel function so callers can import as a named side
        effect. Copy this shape verbatim for `register-structured-output-stream-widget.ts`.
        New widget key: `'structured-output-stream'`. `allowMultiple: true`
        (Summarize produces a new tab per invocation per FR-06). `defaultOrder`
        160 (one past DocumentViewerWidget's 150).
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Fluent v9 semantic-token styling" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/DocumentViewerWidget.tsx">
        `makeStyles` + `tokens.*` references only. NO hex / rgba / `#fff`.
        Dark-mode parity is automatic when semantic tokens are used correctly.
        Patterns to mirror: typography via `tokens.fontSizeBase300` /
        `tokens.fontWeightSemibold`; spacing via `tokens.spacingHorizontal*` /
        `tokens.spacingVerticalM`; borders via `tokens.colorNeutralStroke1`;
        backgrounds via `tokens.colorNeutralBackground1` /
        `tokens.colorNeutralBackground2`.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="PaneEventBus subscription via usePaneEvent" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/events/usePaneEvent.ts">
        Use `usePaneEvent('workspace', (event) =&gt; { ... })` to subscribe.
        Narrow on `event.type` discriminant (`'streaming_started'` /
        `'field_delta'` / `'streaming_complete'`). Unknown event types MUST be
        ignored — return early to preserve back-compat per ADR-030.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Append-only progressive rendering by JSON path" location="N/A — new pattern; document inline">
        Maintain a `Map&lt;string, string&gt;` keyed by `FieldDelta.path` and
        append `content` per delta. Use `useRef` + `useState` carefully: deltas
        arrive faster than React render cycles; batch into a single state
        update via `useReducer` or microtask flushing. Apply visible cursor
        animation (`▋` or Fluent `tokens.colorBrandForeground1` blinking caret
        via CSS keyframes) at the END of the most-recently-updated field while
        streaming is active; remove cursor on `streaming_complete`.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Schema-driven render contract" location="N/A — new pattern; document in widget JSDoc">
        Widget data shape:
        ```typescript
        interface StructuredOutputStreamWidgetData {
          mode: 'streaming' | 'static';     // streaming = subscribe to deltas; static = render from prefilled fields
          schema: StructuredOutputSchema;   // array of field definitions
          prefilledFields?: Record&lt;string, string&gt;;  // for static mode (Insights playbook destination)
          declineState?: { reason: string; suggestedActions?: string[] };  // renders decline UI
          emptyResultState?: boolean;       // renders empty-result hint
          correlationId?: string;           // for matching streaming_started event to this widget instance
        }
        interface StructuredOutputSchema {
          fields: Array&lt;{
            path: string;                   // JSON path key matching FieldDelta.path
            label: string;
            displayHint: 'heading' | 'paragraph' | 'list' | 'badge' | 'callout';
            order: number;
          }&gt;;
        }
        ```
        Concrete schemas for Summarize and Insights playbook MUST be declared
        in module-level `const` exports so consumers (chat-pane dispatcher, D2-16
        renderer) reuse them — not re-declare. Document edge cases (nested
        paths, dynamic field counts e.g. `fileHighlights[N]`) as TODO comments
        for follow-up; v1 may handle `fileHighlights[]` via a single list
        renderer if simpler.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      R5's vertical slice produces structured Summarize output (TL;DR, summary,
      per-file highlights, mentioned parties, call-to-action) that streams via
      SSE `FieldDelta` events. The R5 platform-extensibility claim hinges on the
      SAME widget rendering Insights playbook output (different schema:
      structured envelope from PlaybookExecutionEngine) and Insights RAG
      decline-to-find responses. Reusability across two consumers is the proof
      point for SC-19 (configuration-only follow-on) — `/analyze` in Phase 3
      will be the third consumer, requiring zero widget code change.

      ChatGPT/Claude-style progressive rendering is a deliberate UX choice — users
      see the model "think" rather than wait for a plop. This is the most-visible
      surface in R5; the polish bar is high. Cursor animation at the active
      field tail + smooth append (no layout jitter) are required.

      Risk UR-02 is the schema-driven complexity. The 80/20 mitigation: only the
      Summarize schema and the Insights playbook schema are required for R5
      Phase 2. Insights RAG path uses citation-grounded prose (D2-16 paragraph
      renderer + clickable `[n]` citation tokens) and may use a SIMPLER variant
      of this widget OR a sibling. Decline + empty-result states are first-class
      render states baked into THIS widget for both consumers.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="016" status="not-started">
        Task 016 (D2-06) adds five additive PaneEventBus event types per ADR-030,
        including the three this widget subscribes to: `workspace.streaming_started`,
        `workspace.field_delta`, `workspace.streaming_complete`. This widget
        imports those types from `PaneEventTypes.ts`. Task 016 MUST be ✅ before
        task 017 starts implementation; the dependency is hard.
      </dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>R4 task 042 (W-4) created `DocumentViewerWidget` + its registration
        file as the canonical workspace widget pattern. Task 017 mirrors that
        pattern exactly — registration file shape, FluentLayout, registry key
        naming, lazy-import dynamic loading.</item>
      <item>Insights Engine R2 contract v1.1 (Wave F) produces `answer` SSE
        deltas for RAG-path responses; R5's `FieldDelta` and Insights v1.1 SSE
        protocols are aligned by negotiation (per UR-03). When Wave F deploys,
        the Insights renderer (D2-16 / task 026) will consume this widget in
        STREAMING mode for playbook outputs, STATIC mode for RAG prose path.</item>
      <item>Task 026 (D2-16 — Two-path response renderer) is the
        DOWNSTREAM consumer. It MUST be unblocked by this widget's reusable
        contract. If the contract is brittle, UR-02 materializes — escalate per
        CLAUDE.md §6.</item>
      <item>Task 018 (D2-09 — `FilePreviewContextWidget`) is the parallel sibling
        in P2-G4. Independent widget; no shared code; runs in parallel.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + RIGOR LEVEL">
      Check context usage. If &gt; 70%, create handoff summary and request `/compact`.
      Declare RIGOR LEVEL: FULL per CLAUDE.md §8 (frontend widget on critical
      path; risk UR-02; downstream consumer task 026 depends on contract; 6+
      steps; tags include `widget` + `streaming` + `react-19`).

      Required output (non-negotiable):
      ```
      🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL
      📋 REASON: Frontend widget on R5 critical path, schema-driven design flagged as risk UR-02, downstream consumer (D2-16) depends on stable contract, dark-mode test required, quality gates at Step 9.5.
      📖 PROTOCOL STEPS TO EXECUTE: Step 0 → 1 → 2 → 3 (schema design) → 4 (progressive rendering) → 5 (FieldDelta subscription) → 6 (4 render states) → 7 (dark mode test) → 8 (registration + verification) → 9 (acceptance criteria walk-through) → 9.5 (code-review + adr-check) → 10 (document + complete).
      Proceeding with Step 0...
      ```
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Read `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md` and confirm task 017 status is 🔲, dependency
      016 is ✅, parallel-safe = true (sibling 018 may be in flight). Read
      `current-task.md` to verify no conflicting R5 task is in flight. Confirm
      task 026 (D2-16) is downstream-pending. If task 016 is not ✅, STOP and
      report blocker.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read every file in &lt;inputs&gt; and &lt;knowledge&gt;. Specifically:
      (a) read `PaneEventTypes.ts` to find the additive event types added by
      task 016 (`WorkspaceStreamingStartedEvent`, `WorkspaceFieldDeltaEvent`,
      `WorkspaceStreamingCompleteEvent`); (b) read `DocumentViewerWidget.tsx`
      and its registration file to mirror the structure exactly; (c) read
      `usePaneEvent.ts` to understand the subscription hook signature; (d) read
      ADR-021 + ADR-022 + ADR-030 in full; (e) read spec.md FR-02, FR-06, NFR-09,
      NFR-10, UR-02 in full; (f) skim `BUILD-A-NEW-WORKSPACE-WIDGET.md` for any
      additional conventions (Pattern D vs composable section).
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Design Schema-Driven Render Contract">
      Define the `StructuredOutputStreamWidgetData` interface + `StructuredOutputSchema`
      shape in module-level exports per the pattern documented in &lt;knowledge&gt;.
      Author two CONCRETE schemas as module-level `const` exports:
      `SUMMARIZE_SCHEMA` (TL;DR, summary, per-file highlights, mentioned parties,
      call-to-action) and `INSIGHTS_PLAYBOOK_SCHEMA` (envelope fields per Insights
      contract v1.1). Each schema entry specifies `path`, `label`, `displayHint`,
      `order`. Display hints supported in v1: `'heading'`, `'paragraph'`, `'list'`,
      `'badge'`, `'callout'`. Document edge cases (dynamic-cardinality fields
      like `fileHighlights[N]`) as JSDoc TODOs for follow-up; v1 may render
      `fileHighlights[]` via a single list renderer keyed by a synthetic path
      pattern (`fileHighlights.*`) — decision: render as a Fluent v9 `Card` per
      element with the heading + paragraph hint pair. Apply 80/20 per UR-02.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Implement Progressive Rendering Core">
      Build the widget's core rendering engine:
      (a) State: `useReducer` with `Map&lt;string, { content: string; lastSequence: number }&gt;`
      keyed by JSON path; action types `{ type: 'streaming_started', correlationId }`,
      `{ type: 'field_delta', path, content, sequence }`, `{ type: 'streaming_complete' }`,
      `{ type: 'reset' }`.
      (b) Out-of-order handling: compare `sequence` against `lastSequence` per
      path; ignore stale deltas (log via `console.debug` for telemetry).
      (c) Append semantics: new content appended to existing per `path`.
      (d) Cursor animation: render `tokens.colorBrandForeground1` blinking caret
      via CSS keyframes (`@keyframes pulse-cursor { 0%, 100% { opacity: 1 } 50% { opacity: 0 } }`)
      at the END of the most-recently-updated field; track `mostRecentPath` in
      reducer state. Remove cursor on `streaming_complete` action.
      (e) Render order: iterate `schema.fields` by `order` ascending; for each
      field, look up `state.get(field.path)?.content` and render via the
      appropriate Fluent v9 primitive matching `field.displayHint`.
      (f) Smooth append: avoid layout shift by reserving vertical space via
      `min-height` on field containers; use `Skeleton` placeholder for fields
      that have no content yet during streaming.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Wire FieldDelta Subscription">
      Subscribe to the `workspace` channel via `usePaneEvent('workspace', handler)`.
      In the handler, narrow on `event.type`:
      (a) `'streaming_started'` — dispatch `{ type: 'reset' }` to clear prior
      state if `correlationId` matches this widget instance's
      `widgetData.correlationId`. Otherwise ignore (other widget instance).
      (b) `'field_delta'` — dispatch `{ type: 'field_delta', path, content, sequence }`
      after correlation-id match check.
      (c) `'streaming_complete'` — dispatch `{ type: 'streaming_complete' }`
      after correlation-id match.
      (d) Any other `event.type` — return early (preserve ADR-030 unknown-type
      tolerance).

      Correlation: in `mode: 'streaming'`, the dispatcher (chat-pane SSE
      consumer) emits `streaming_started` with the correlation-id that was
      passed into the widget's `widgetData.correlationId` at mount time.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Implement Four Render States">
      Render-state matrix MUST be visually distinct:
      (a) **Streaming** — schema fields render progressively; visible cursor on
      most-recent-field tail; `Skeleton` placeholders for not-yet-streamed
      fields; subtle `Badge` (e.g. "Streaming…") in header.
      (b) **Streaming complete** — final formatted output with no cursor;
      header `Badge` removed or replaced with "Complete" indicator (semantic
      `tokens.colorPaletteGreenBackground2`); fully formatted Fluent v9 typography.
      (c) **Decline** (Insights decline-to-find) — when
      `widgetData.declineState` is set, render Fluent v9 `MessageBar` with
      `intent="warning"`, the `reason` text, and `suggestedActions` as a Fluent
      `Button` list below. Hide schema-field rendering entirely.
      (d) **Empty-result** — when `widgetData.emptyResultState === true`,
      render muted `Text` with copy "I couldn't find anything for that. Try
      rephrasing or attaching files." (per spec FR-13 / D2-16 acceptance) +
      `tokens.colorNeutralForeground3` styling. Hide schema-field rendering.

      The four states are mutually exclusive in render output; widget validates
      via TypeScript discriminated union OR runtime guard. Default state:
      streaming (mode: 'streaming') OR static rendering of `prefilledFields`
      (mode: 'static') — these are sub-modes of "streaming complete" UX-wise.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Dark Mode + Visual Verification">
      Verify all four render states render legibly against both `webLightTheme`
      and `webDarkTheme`. Use the existing test harness in
      `src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/__tests__/` if
      it has dark-mode coverage; otherwise run the widget in the SpaarkeAi shell
      (or a Storybook story if available) with dark-mode active and capture
      visual evidence for task notes. Confirm: no hex/rgba in styles; semantic
      tokens only; cursor color uses brand foreground token; decline `MessageBar`
      uses `intent="warning"` semantic styling; empty-result hint uses
      `colorNeutralForeground3`. Document evidence in task notes.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Register Widget + Verify Build">
      Create `register-structured-output-stream-widget.ts` mirroring
      `register-document-viewer-widget.ts`:
      - `STRUCTURED_OUTPUT_STREAM_WIDGET_TYPE = 'structured-output-stream'`
      - `allowMultiple: true` (FR-06 — each Summarize invocation = new tab)
      - `defaultOrder: 160` (one past DocumentViewerWidget's 150)
      - `displayName: 'Structured AI Output'`
      - `category: 'analysis'` (or matching existing category — verify in registry)
      - `icon: 'TextBulletListSquareSparkleRegular'` or similar Fluent icon
      - Lazy import via `() =&gt; import('./StructuredOutputStreamWidget')`

      Add a sentinel `registerStructuredOutputStreamWidget()` named-export
      function per the canonical pattern. Add the side-effect import in the
      package barrel (or shell entry-point per existing pattern).

      Build: `npm run build` in `src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/`. Verify
      no TypeScript errors, no new lint warnings. Verify the widget appears in
      `WorkspaceWidgetRegistry` enumeration (smoke check via test or console).
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Verify Acceptance Criteria">
      Walk through every &lt;acceptance-criterion&gt; below and confirm each is
      testable + passing. Record evidence per criterion in task notes.
      Specifically verify the reusability claim: stub a hypothetical D2-16
      consumer call (Insights playbook static rendering) with
      `mode: 'static'` + `INSIGHTS_PLAYBOOK_SCHEMA` + `prefilledFields` and
      confirm the widget renders correctly WITHOUT any widget code change.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `code-review` skill against the new files
      (`StructuredOutputStreamWidget.tsx` + `register-structured-output-stream-widget.ts`).
      Run `adr-check` skill against the same files; verify:
      - ADR-021 (Fluent v9 semantic tokens + dark mode) PASS
      - ADR-022 (React 19) PASS
      - ADR-012 (component lib placement) PASS
      - ADR-030 (additive PaneEventBus types; no new channel) PASS
      - ADR-010 (DI minimalism — N/A confirmed)
      - ADR-029 (BFF publish hygiene — N/A confirmed; frontend-only)

      Both gates MUST pass before marking the task complete. If either fails,
